coming correspondence to provide timely support and intervention. Manual processing of thousands of daily letters was time-consuming and could delay critical support for at-risk individuals.</p>\",\"solution\":\"<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">Whitemail is an AI-powered vulnerability detection tool that scans incoming post from benefit claimants to identify potentially vulnerable customers requiring urgent support. The system uses natural language processing to digitally read text from scanned images of letters, with personal information removed, to quickly identify customers who may be at risk. All AI-identified cases are reviewed by experienced DWP staff who assess and determine appropriate support actions.</p>\",\"results\":\"<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">Since going live in 2023, Whitemail processes correspondence in real-time rather than the weeks it previously took.</p>\\n<ul class=\\\"govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-list--spaced\\\">\\n<li>Processing Volume: 22,000 documents daily in real time</li>\\n<li>Total Documents: 2.2 million documents processed using AI technology (as of Aug 2024)</li>\\n<li>Speed Improvement: Same-day processing (previously took weeks)</li>\\n</ul>\",\"learnings\":\"\",\"links\":[{\"text\":\"Policy paper (April 2025): Advanced Customer Support - Delivering support and transformation to help DWP customers with additional support needs\",\"url\":\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/delivering-support-and-transformation-to-help-dwp-customers-with-additional-support-needs/advanced-customer-support-delivering-support-and-transformation-to-help-dwp-customers-with-additional-support-needs#identifying-when-someone-needs-additional-support-1\"},{\"text\":\"Article (Aug 2024): DWP grows trials of generative AI and reports 'no immediate concerns' from fairness assessment of fraud algorithm\",\"url\":\"https://www.publictechnology.net/2024/08/16/society-and-welfare/dwp-grows-trials-of-generative-ai-and-reports-no-immediate-concerns-from-fa