ration tool was developed to enforce nine distinct moderation rules. It combines deterministic checks, such as detecting URLs, email addresses, and profanity, with custom machine learning models trained on NHS.UK content. Reviews flagged for safeguarding concerns or disputed by users are escalated to human moderators. This ensures expert oversight where necessary. The system provides instant feedback to users, allowing them to edit and resubmit reviews promptly.</p>\",\"results\":\"<ul class=\\\"govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-list--spaced\\\">\\n<li>Moderation time reduced from several days to just seconds, enabling near-instant feedback to users.</li>\\n<li>Increased publication rates, with more reviews successfully published due to immediate detection of policy breaches, unlike the previous manual process where many rejected reviews were never resubmitted.</li>\\n<li>Significant cost savings achieved by eliminating reliance on expensive third-party moderation services, while enabling efficient scaling as review volumes grow.</li>\\n<li>ML models match or exceed human performance, delivering consistent and accurate policy enforcement across all reviews.</li>\\n<li>First AI product to receive clinical approval on NHS.UK.</li>\\n</ul>\",\"links\":[{\"text\":\"Read the full technical details in the Algorithmic Transparency Recording Standard repository\",\"url\":\"https://www.gov.uk/algorithmic-transparency-records/nhs-england-nhs-dot-uk-reviews-automoderation-tool\"},{\"text\":\"Read the full case study in the AI Playbook for the UK Government\",\"url\":\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ai-playbook-for-the-uk-government/artificial-intelligence-playbook-for-the-uk-government-html#nhsuk-reviews-an-automated-reviews-moderator\"},{\"text\":\"Explore the project page\",\"url\":\"https://nhsengland.github.io/datascience/our_work/ratings-and-reviews/\"},{\"text\":\"Explore the code for the Reviews Automoderation Tool on GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/