type, age, and floor area, alongside an imputation model to fill gaps in missing data. These predictions are matched with benefits data from the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) to identify eligible households. A rigorous appeals process allows customers to challenge decisions if they believe they are eligible for the scheme.</p>\",\"results\":\"<ul class=\\\"govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-list--spaced\\\">\\n<li>In 2023/24, over 90% of the total 3 million rebates were issued automatically. </li>\\n<li>The implementation of this solution has made the process fairer by eliminating the first-come, first-served system. As a result, vulnerable customers who may not have been aware of the support available are now proactively identified and included.</li>\\n</ul>\",\"links\":[{\"text\":\"Read the full technical details in the Algorithmic Transparency Recording Standard repository\",\"url\":\"https://www.gov.uk/algorithmic-transparency-records/desnz-warm-home-discount-eligibility-energy-cost-modelling\"}]}","url":"/tools/warm-home-discount-energy-cost-predictor/","type":"use-case"},{"title":"Hawkeye Service","synopsis":"Streamlining economic data management","content":"{\"title\":\"Hawkeye Service\",\"category\":\"Collect and clean data\",\"subcategory\":\"General tasks\",\"created\":\"1757915486584\",\"updated\":\"1757915486584\",\"synopsis\":\"Streamlining economic data management\",\"draft\":true,\"organisation\":\"HM Treasury (HMT)\",\"governmentBody\":\"UK Government\",\"userGroup\":\"Civil Servants\",\"useCaseType\":\"Specific\",\"typeOfTechnology\":\"Data or Infrastructure\",\"impact\":\"Time Savings / Improved Efficiency\",\"phase\":\"Live\",\"challenge\":\"<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">Treasury analysts and economists frequently performed repetitive tasks such as downloading and transforming datasets like ONS inflation data, creating duplication of effort, dataset divergence, and operational inefficiencies. </p>\",\"solution\":\"<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">Hawkeye is a centralised data management system built on Microsoft Fabric cloud analytics platform with Power BI integrations that automates economic data collection from Treasury's internal sources and external partners including the Office for National Statistics (ONS). The system generates automated flash briefings with key economic data summaries, eliminates manual data transformation through automated backend processes, provides an accessible front-end interface where coding is optional, and centralises data management to create a one-stop shop for data and analysis across the department.</p>\",\"results\":\"<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">Hawkeye is currently live and widely used across the Treasury. It has won top honours at the Treasury Information Systems (TrIS) Innovation Awards for transforming data management operations. The tool has saved hours of analysts' time and allows them to focus on deeper economic analysis and strategic work.</p>\",\"links\":[{\"text\":\"Article (Feb 2025): Award-winning Innovation at HM Treasury: how Hawkeye is transforming data management - Government Transformation\",\"url\":\"https://www.government-transformation.com/transformation/award-winning-innovation-at-hm-treasury-how-hawkeye-is-transforming-data-management\"}]}","url":"/tools/hawkeye-service/","type":"use-case"},{"title":"Content Education Store","synopsis":"Enabling better AI tools through curated educational content","content":"{\"title\":\"Content Education Store\",\"category\":\"Collect and clean data\",\"subcategory\":\"General tasks\",\"created\":\"1747126641652\",\"updated\":\"1749713957540\",\"synopsis\":\"Enabling better AI tools through curated educational content\",\"draft\":true,\"organisation\":\"Department for Education (DfE)\",\"governmentBody\":\"UK Government\",\"userGroup\":\"General Public\",\"useCaseType\":\"Specific\",\"typeOfTechnology\":\"Data or Infrastructure\",\"impact\":\"Better Customer Experience / Improved Efficiency\",\"challenge\":\"<p 