y represented CPIN information</li>\\n<li><strong>54% would continue</strong> using the tool (indicating moderate adoption)</li>\\n<li><strong>75% suggested</strong> tool could be further developed to integrate more sources</li>\\n<li><strong>5% not confident</strong> in tool accuracy</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\"><em>Mixed user feedback being analysed for improvement opportunities and potential broader rollout.</em></p>\",\"links\":[{\"text\":\"Research and analysis (April 2025): Evaluation of AI trials in the asylum decision making process\",\"url\":\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-ai-trials-in-the-asylum-decision-making-process/evaluation-of-ai-trials-in-the-asylum-decision-making-process\"}]}","url":"/tools/asylum-policy-search-(aps)/","type":"use-case"},{"title":"Ask HMRC Online","synopsis":"Supporting taxpayers with AI-powered query resolution","content":"{\"title\":\"Ask HMRC Online\",\"category\":\"Find information\",\"subcategory\":\"General tasks\",\"created\":\"1757697577360\",\"updated\":\"1757697577361\",\"synopsis\":\"Supporting taxpayers with AI-powered query resolution\",\"draft\":true,\"organisation\":\"HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC)\",\"governmentBody\":\"UK Government\",\"userGroup\":\"General Public\",\"useCaseType\":\"Reusable\",\"typeOfTechnology\":\"Machine Learning\",\"impact\":\"Better Customer Experience / Time Savings / Cost Savings / Improved Efficiency\",\"phase\":\"Live\",\"challenge\":\"<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">HMRC needed to provide 24/7 tax support to millions of UK taxpayers and businesses while reducing the burden on human advisers who were handling repetitive, basic tax queries that traditionally required phone calls or manual support.</p>\",\"solution\":\"<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">Ask HMRC Online is a digital assistant that uses Natural Language Understanding and intent classification to provide instant responses to common tax queries. The system operates through HMRC's Multi-Channel Dig