elivery planning).\\n\\nStep 3: Build the Business Case: Using my inputs, produce a structured business case outline with clear sections for each of the five cases. Under each section, provide concise content or bullet points that align with Green Book guidance and HM Treasury best practices – for example, ensuring the Strategic Case demonstrates clear alignment to policy objectives, the Economic Case includes cost-benefit analysis and optimism bias adjustments, and the Management Case outlines governance per Cabinet Office standards (GovS 002) and an evaluation plan per the Magenta Book.\\n\\nStep 4: Value for Money & Assurance: Highlight areas that ensure value for money (e.g. cost-benefit ratio, affordability) and compliance with IPA guidance and NAO expectations (such as demonstrating robust options appraisal and benefits management. \\n\\n//Style and tone\\n\\nEnsure the tone is formal and evidence-based, ready for senior scrutiny.\\n\"}","url":"/prompts/write-a-business-case/"},{"title":"Scan for project consequences","type":"prompt","synopsis":"Scan your project for potential financial, social, environmental, reputational, and legal consequences. ","content":"{\"title\":\"Scan for project consequences\",\"created\":\"1749221057262\",\"updated\":\"1763914596842\",\"description\":\"Scan your project for potential financial, social, environmental, reputational, and legal consequences. \",\"category\":\"Analyse data and text\",\"subcategory\":\"Check compliance and standards\",\"tags\":\"project management\",\"use\":\"\",\"content\":\"<div class=\\\"govuk-inset-text\\\">\\n  Check the results from this prompt for accuracy, as AI can make mistakes and the library has not been formally evaluated. \\n</div>\\n<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">Email ai-knowledge-hub@dsit.gov.uk to share feedback about this prompt.</p>\\n<h2 class=\\\"govuk-heading-m\\\" id=\\\"whatthispromptdoes\\\">What this prompt does</h2>\\n<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">This prompt is suitable for any AI