cture: the game consists of three rounds; each focused on improving a prompt collaboratively. \\n\\nIntroduction: you explain the purpose of the game and its relevance to project delivery work. \\n\\nTeam Context: ask me to name a team (e.g. “Energy Security”) going out for a meal. This becomes the basis for the initial prompt. \\n\\nInitial Prompt: you generate a basic prompt (e.g. “Write a story about the Energy Security team going out for a meal.”) \\n\\nIteration: we take turns refining the prompt to improve its clarity, creativity, and effectiveness. \\n\\nScoring & Feedback: after each round, you score my version using the following criteria: \\n\\nPurposefulness (1–5): does the prompt clearly support a specific goal or outcome? Purposefulness (1–5): is the prompt specific and easy to understand? \\n\\nEffectiveness (1–5): does the prompt guide Copilot to produce a high-quality response? You also provide a prompt engineering tip after each round. \\n\\nFinal Prompt: At the end of Round 3, we run the final version as a demonstration of learning. Scoring: Each round is scored out of 15 (5 per criterion), with a total score out of 45 at the end. This helps track progress and identify areas for improvement. Let’s begin.\"}","url":"/prompts/improve-your-prompt-writing-skills/"},{"title":"Improve a simple prompt","type":"prompt","synopsis":"Turn a simple idea into a detailed, high-quality prompt, so you get a better result.","content":"{\"title\":\"Improve a simple prompt\",\"created\":\"1749219544695\",\"updated\":\"1763577907996\",\"description\":\"Turn a simple idea into a detailed, high-quality prompt, so you get a better result.\",\"category\":\"Learning and development\",\"subcategory\":\"Prompt development\",\"tags\":\"Prompt Engineering\",\"content\":\"<div class=\\\"govuk-inset-text\\\">\\n  Check the results from this prompt for accuracy, as AI can make mistakes and the library has not been formally evaluated. \\n</div>\\n<p class=\\\"govuk-body\\\">Email 